Closes #87203

## Summary
- allow managed inbound media references through the host read workspace guard
- normalize `media://inbound/...` to the validated media-store file path before upstream read execution
- cover custom workspace reads with and without `workspaceOnly`

## Verification
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/pi-tools.workspace-paths.test.ts src/agents/pi-tools.read.workspace-root-guard.test.ts src/media/media-reference.test.ts`
- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/pi-tools.read.ts src/agents/pi-tools.ts src/agents/pi-tools.workspace-paths.test.ts`
- `git diff --check`
- `pnpm changed:lanes --json --base upstream/main`

## Real behavior proof
Behavior addressed
- Non-sandbox host read tools now resolve `media://inbound/<id>` against the global OpenClaw media store instead of treating it as a custom-workspace-relative path.

Real environment tested
- Local macOS checkout, no mocks for the proof script.
- Temporary `OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR` with a real `media/inbound/telegram-note.txt` file.
- Separate custom workspace directory named `workspace-regi`.
- Real `createOpenClawCodingTools` read tool with `tools.fs.workspaceOnly: true`.

Exact steps or command run after this patch
```
node --import tsx --input-type=module <<'EOF'
import fs from 'node:fs/promises';
import os from 'node:os';
import path from 'node:path';

const rootDir = await fs.mkdtemp(path.join(os.tmpdir(), 'openclaw-real-media-'));
const stateDir = path.join(rootDir, 'state');
const workspaceDir = path.join(rootDir, 'workspace-regi');
const inboundId = 'telegram-note.txt';
const inboundPath = path.join(stateDir, 'media', 'inbound', inboundId);
await fs.mkdir(path.dirname(inboundPath), { recursive: true });
await fs.mkdir(workspaceDir, { recursive: true });
await fs.writeFile(inboundPath, 'managed inbound read ok', 'utf8');
process.env.OPENCLAW_STATE_DIR = stateDir;

const { createOpenClawCodingTools } = await import('./src/agents/pi-tools.ts');
const tools = createOpenClawCodingTools({
  workspaceDir,
  config: { tools: { fs: { workspaceOnly: true } } },
});
const readTool = tools.find((tool) => tool.name === 'read');
if (!readTool) throw new Error('read tool missing');
const result = await readTool.execute('proof-managed-media', {
  path: `media://inbound/${inboundId}`,
});
const text = (result.content ?? [])
  .filter((block) => block && block.type === 'text')
  .map((block) => block.text)
  .join('\n');
let corruptedWorkspacePathExists = true;
try {
  await fs.access(path.join(workspaceDir, 'media:', 'inbound', inboundId));
} catch {
  corruptedWorkspacePathExists = false;
}
console.log(`customWorkspace=${workspaceDir}`);
console.log(`stateInboundPath=${inboundPath}`);
console.log(`mediaRef=media://inbound/${inboundId}`);
console.log(`workspaceOnly=true`);
console.log(`readContainsManagedContent=${text.includes('managed inbound read ok')}`);
console.log(`workspaceRelativeCorruptionExists=${corruptedWorkspacePathExists}`);
await fs.rm(rootDir, { recursive: true, force: true });
EOF
```

Evidence after fix
```
customWorkspace=/var/folders/sl/5dkd3zq12dv65j6jx57zq1hc0000gn/T/openclaw-real-media-j4EyJ0/workspace-regi
stateInboundPath=/var/folders/sl/5dkd3zq12dv65j6jx57zq1hc0000gn/T/openclaw-real-media-j4EyJ0/state/media/inbound/telegram-note.txt
mediaRef=media://inbound/telegram-note.txt
workspaceOnly=true
readContainsManagedContent=true
workspaceRelativeCorruptionExists=false
```

Observed result after fix
- The read tool returned the managed media file contents.
- No `workspace-regi/media:/inbound/telegram-note.txt` path was created or required.

What was not tested
- Windows runtime execution; the repro logic is covered with path-safe unit tests, but this proof ran on macOS.
- Full `pnpm check:changed`; Crabbox could not run from this shell because AWS requires broker login and `blacksmith` is not installed for `blacksmith-testbox`.

